The paper deals with the reconstruction of 3D geometry from visual scenes, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and mobile robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed in the paper involves Bayesian inference, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence, and can be applied to a wide range of problems, including those in neuroscience (cs.NE), electronic design automation (cs.ET), and control systems (cs.SY).
